Vamos práticar com outros exemplo:
*********************************

BRUTE FORCE (T1110)
Ataque (simulação)

for i in {1..10}; do ssh fakeuser@localhost; done

Digite senha errada várias vezes
Logs gerados

Arquivo: /var/log/auth.log

Eventos:
- Failed password
- Invalid user

Detecção no Splunk - spl

Para IPv4 - spl

index=linux sourcetype=linux_secure "Failed password"
| stats count by src_ip, user
| where count > 5

Para IPv6 - spl

index=* "Failed password"
| rex "from (?<src_ip>[^\s]+)"
| bin _time span=1m
| stats count by _time, src_ip
| where count > 5

 Detecção avançada - spl

index=linux sourcetype=linux_secure ("Failed password" OR "Invalid user")
| bucket _time span=1m
| stats count by _time, src_ip
| where count > 10

Outra versão - spl

index=* ("Failed password" OR "Invalid user")
| rex "from (?<src_ip>[^\s]+)"
| bucket _time span=1m
| stats count by _time, src_ip
| where count > 10

Aida, outra versão - spl

index=* ("Failed password" OR "Invalid user")
| rex "from (?<src_ip>[^\s]+)"
| rex "for (invalid user )?(?<user>\S+)"
| bucket _time span=1m
| stats count by _time, src_ip, user
| where count > 5


Ver extração de IP  - spl
index=* "Failed password"
| rex "from (?<src_ip>[^\s]+)"
| table src_ip


Ver contagem  - spl
index=* "Failed password"
| rex "from (?<src_ip>[^\s]+)"
| stats count by src_ip


